Our clients reach their first $100K per month in a 12 months or less by:

✅ Focusing on one offer, finding that one audience it will serve, and cornering the one channel to connect with that audience. 

✅ Tweaking their offer to make sure they can deliver transformational and highly valuable outcomes.

You’ve hustled and you've finally hit that $100K/month mark. 

HUGE congrats 🎉... but now what? 

You’re probably discovering that what got you here WON’T get you there. 

What am I talking about? 

Scaling.

Scaling isn’t just a buzzword; it’s the necessary evolution of your business. 

And if you're serious about going beyond $100K/month, let's get one thing straight: 

You NEED a Sales Team and Robust Sales Systems. 

No exceptions.🚀

💥 Why a Sales Team?

1️⃣ Skill Diversity: One person can't be an expert in everything. A dedicated sales team brings a variety of skills to the table—negotiation, lead qualification, closing, etc.

2️⃣ Time: Let's be real, you only have so many hours in a day. A sales team frees up your time so you can focus on business strategy and client delivery.

3️⃣ Consistency: A good sales team keeps the pipeline full and deals closing, providing the revenue consistency needed to scale.

💡 And Sales Systems?

1️⃣ Scalability: A solid sales process can be scaled quickly. Imagine having a sales playbook that any new team member can pick up and run with!

2️⃣ Predictability: With a sales system, you'll know your numbers. Cost to acquire, lifetime value, and so on. This data is critical for making informed decisions.

3️⃣ Accountability: A clear sales process means that everyone knows their responsibilities. That makes tracking performance and accountability simpler.

⏰ Time to Act!

If you’re committed to creating impactful, scalable growth, then building out your sales team and systems should be your next focus. 

And let's be clear, it's not just about having 'a' system or 'a' team, but the RIGHT systems and the RIGHT team.

So stop thinking small and start building. 

Your dreams aren’t going to realize themselves! 🚀
